claim.claim-text:
20. A method of increasing power from an internal combustion engine comprising:
raising the amount of air taken into the internal combustion engine, with an electronically controlled supercharger;
conditioning air taken into the internal combustion engine through an exchanger with an active element;
sensing operational demands through a sensor collection;
controlling operational demands with sensor interface and smart controller operation;
buffering system power to reduce parasitics and extend operation duration;
interfacing the smart controller to a host vehicle engine control unit interoperation; and
displaying system operational information for monitoring and controlling of system functions.
